title: Same Girl New Songs- All American Rejects Demo
description:
Same Girl, New Songs was a self-released Demo CD made by The All-American Rejects in 2001. At the time, the band consisted of high school friends Tyson Ritter and Nick Wheeler from Stillwater, OK. The CD consists of songs written by Ritter and Wheeler, and was a combination of two previous demos. The songs "One More Sad Song", "Drive Away", "Too Far Gone", and "Don't Leave Me" were re-recorded for their label debut, self-titled release in 2002. This CD is rare, because it was produced by the band themselves, was only available at shows, and is no longer produced.
